# Orchestrator — Cursor Rules

## Overview
Desktop app (Tauri) that orchestrates local Spring Boot and JavaScript projects.
Two modules: `orchestrator-core` (Java 17) and `orchestrator-desktop` (Tauri + React).
The old `orchestrator-ui/` module is DEPRECATED — all frontend lives in `orchestrator-desktop/src/`.

## Architecture

```
orchestrator-core/          Java 17, fat JAR, stdin/stdout JSON IPC
orchestrator-desktop/       Tauri (Rust) + React/Vite/Tailwind
  ├── src/                  React frontend (TSX)
  ├── src-tauri/src/main.rs Rust bridge (CoreBridge)
  └── src-tauri/tauri.conf  Tauri config
```

### IPC Flow
UI (React) → invoke("core_request") → Rust (main.rs CoreBridge)
→ stdin JSON → Java Core (CoreRuntime.handle) → stdout JSON → Rust → UI

### IPC Protocol
Request:  `{"id":"uuid","method":"methodName","params":{...}}`
Response: `{"id":"uuid","ok":true,"result":{...},"error":null}`
Event:    `{"event":"eventName","payload":{...}}` (emitted as core_event to UI)

## Core Module (Java 17)

### Key Classes
| Class | Responsibility | Package |
|-------|---------------|---------|
| Main | Entry point, reads stdin, dispatches to CoreRuntime | core |
| CoreRuntime | Method dispatch, lifecycle | core.runtime |
| WorkspaceManager | Roots, scan, persistence | core.runtime |
| ServiceManager | Start/stop/restart, status refresh | core.runtime |
| ContainerManager | Container CRUD, service linking | core.runtime |
| LogManager | Log subscriptions, emit lines | core.runtime |
| ProjectScanner | Walk dirs, find pom.xml, detect Spring Boot | core.runtime |
| JsProjectScanner | Walk dirs, find package.json, detect Next/Nest/React/Vue | core.runtime |
| PortExtractor | Read port from application.properties/yml | core.runtime |
| ExternalToolLauncher | Open folder/terminal/editor | core.runtime |
| StateStore | JSON read/write to files | core.runtime |
| ProcessManager | Process start/stop/kill, alive check | process |

### Models
| Model | Type | Fields |
|-------|------|--------|
| ServiceDefinition | Lombok @Data | name, path, command, logFile, env, javaHome, javaVersion, containerIds, projectType, availableScripts |
| ProjectType | Enum | SPRING_BOOT, NEXT, NEST, REACT, VUE, UNKNOWN |
| ServiceDescriptor | Lombok @Data | definition, runtime |
| ServiceRuntime | Lombok @Data | pid, status, lastStartAt, lastStopAt, lastError |
| Container | Lombok @Data | id, name, description |
| ServiceStatus | Enum | RUNNING, STOPPED, ERROR |
| ServiceView | Record | Flattened DTO for IPC responses |
| IpcRequest | Record | id, method, params |
| IpcResponse | Record | id, ok, result, error |
| IpcError | Record | code, message |
| IpcEvent | Record | event, payload |

### IPC Methods (CoreRuntime.handle)
- ping, getWorkspace, setExcludeDirs
- importRootAndScan, importRootsAndScan, removeRoot, scanRoots
- listServices, startService, stopService, restartService, startAll, stopAll
- removeService
- subscribeLogs, unsubscribeLogs
- createContainer, updateContainer, deleteContainer, listContainers
- addServiceToContainer, removeServiceFromContainer, getServicesByContainer
- startContainer, stopContainer
- openServiceFolder, openServiceTerminal, openServiceInEditor

### Persistence
- `workspace.json` — roots, services, containers, removedServices (exclusion set)
- `runtime.json` — per-service runtime state (pid, status, timestamps)
- Both in `--stateDir` directory

### Critical Business Rules
- Container deletion NEVER removes services — only clears containerIds
- scanRoots() preserves existing containerIds by merging on service name
- Stale containerIds (referencing deleted containers) are cleaned during scan
- Removed services tracked in `workspace.removedServices`; excluded from scan
- importRootAndScan clears removedServices when adding a new root
- importRootsAndScan: folders with pom.xml added as direct services, others as roots
- Service removal clears containerIds before removing
- Ports auto-detected from application.properties/yml, fallback to hash-based

## Desktop Module (Tauri + React)

### Rust (src-tauri/src/main.rs)
- CoreBridge: spawns Java JAR, manages stdin/stdout
- core_request: Tauri command, sends IPC request, waits for response
- select_folder: Tauri dialog for multi-folder selection (pipe-separated)
- get/set runtime settings: persist desktop-only config in `desktop-settings.json`
- Java startup accepts a custom Java folder or executable from Settings and restarts the core after save
- Events emitted as "core_event" to UI

### React Components
| Component | Path | Responsibility |
|-----------|------|---------------|
| App | ui/App.tsx | Layout, state, keyboard shortcuts |
| ServiceTable | ui/ServiceTable.tsx | Service list, actions |
| ContextMenu | ui/ContextMenu.tsx | Service context menu with hover submenus |
| ContainersPanel | ui/ContainersPanel.tsx | Container CRUD, start/stop container |
| LogsPanel | ui/LogsPanel.tsx | Log stream, search, copy, level colors, monitor tab |
| MonitorPanel | ui/MonitorPanel.tsx | Aggregated container logs with colored service badges |
| StatusBar | ui/StatusBar.tsx | Running/stopped/error counts |
| Toast | ui/Toast.tsx | Toast notifications + useToast hook |
| ImportSection | ui/ImportSection.tsx | Root path import form |

### API Client (api/client.ts)
- All methods go through `core<T>(method, params)` which calls `invoke("core_request")`
- Types in `api/types.ts`: ServiceDto, ContainerDto, WorkspaceDto, StopResultDto

### Keyboard Shortcuts
- Ctrl+S: start selected service
- Ctrl+X: stop selected service
- Ctrl+R: restart selected service
- Ctrl+F: search in logs

## Build
- `./build.sh` — full build: core JAR → copy to Tauri → frontend build → Tauri build
- `./start.sh` — dev mode: core JAR → Vite dev → Tauri dev
- `scripts/install/install.sh` — install automático para macOS/Linux via release latest
- `scripts/install/install.ps1` — install automático para Windows via release latest
- Output: `.app`/`.dmg` in `orchestrator-desktop/src-tauri/target/release/bundle/`

## Runtime Requirements
- Released desktop app bundles the core JAR but still launches it with system `java`
- End-user machine must have Java 17+ available on `PATH`
- `JAVA_HOME` is the recommended default JDK for Spring Boot services
- If `java` is not found, the desktop Settings panel can persist a custom Java home or `java.exe` path
- End users do not need Rust, Maven, or Node.js to open the desktop app itself
- Node.js and Maven are only needed when imported services depend on them or when developing the repo

## Tech Stack
- Java 17 (Maven, Jackson, Lombok for models)
- Rust (Tauri 2.x)
- React 18, TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind CSS
- No Spring Boot in core (plain Java + Jackson)

## Conventions
- Container = logical group of services (NOT Docker)
- Service = Spring Boot project discovered via pom.xml scan
- All IPC is synchronous request/response except log events (async stream)
- State persisted as JSON files, no database
- Max 300 lines per file
- No comments in code
- Portuguese for UI text, English for code identifiers
